            . I am a <rs id="t17731208-16-viclabel79" type="occupation">hackney coachman</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t17731208-16-victim240 t17731208-16-viclabel79"></join>, and live in <placeName id="t17731208-16-crimeloc80">Warner-street, Cold-Bath-fields</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t17731208-16-crimeloc80" type="placeName" value="Warner-street, Cold-Bath-fields"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t17731208-16-crimeloc80" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t17731208-16-off78 t17731208-16-crimeloc80"></join>; Mr. Walker, another coachman, keeps coaches in the same yard with myself; the prisoner was a helper to us both; I missed oats several times; I was told the prisoner had confessed stealing them; I took them before Justice Girdler; there he confessed he had taken oats twice from my lost in Red-Lion-yard, where the stables are; the oats stand now in a sack; I have not measured it; I cannot positively swear it is my parcel of oats, but the prisoner positively owned they were the oats he had taken from me.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t17731208-16-person242">
                  William
                   Roper
